commitResults.messageBody:
Developer Guide contains information for AddressBook.

Let's add and edit
* target user profile
* value proposition
* user stories
* use cases
* glossary
to reflect information for TAskmaster.

AddressBook3 uses AddressBook and Person in its code.

Let's refactor these to Taskmaster and Student respectively.

AddressBook does not have attendance feature.

Users of TAskmaster will be able to mark their students' attendance.

Let's add an attendance class to represent a list of students'
attendance.

Users should have a way to mark the attendance of their students.

Let's implement the Attendance feature to allow them to do so.

GUI requires an ObservableList to display students' attendances.

Let's
* implement an Attendance class that represents a student's attendance
* implement an AttendanceList class that represents a list of students'
attendances

Ui needs to get name from nusnetId.

Let's create a named attendance class that encapsulates an attendance
object and the name of the student with that nusnetId.

AttendanceList is in ModelManager

Code will follow OOP principles better if it was shifted into
Taskmaster.

Let's shift attendanceList into Taskmaster and reorganize code.

Name is separated from Attendance of student and GUI displays
data to the user based on NamedAttendance

In v1.3, sessions and class participation will be added.

Let's
* Refactor Attendance to StudentRecord
* Remove NamedAttendance and shift Name of student into StudentRecord
* Add a ClassParticipation to each StudentRecord

Add feature to mark all students' attendance
commitResults.messageBody:
To mark attendance of all students, users have to do so for each
of the students, one by one.

Let's improve the usability of TAskmaster by adding a feature to
mark the attendance of all students in the list with one command.

commitResults.messageBody:
JavaFX ObservableList notifys the GUI to update when items are added or
deleted, but not when items are edited.

This results in the GUI not updating when a student's attendance is
marked (and their respective student record changed).

Let's make StudentRecord immutable so that whenever a student's record
is updated, the GUI will update correspondingly.

commitResults.messageTitle: Redesign GUI of Student List and Session buttons
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's redesign how the student list and session looks to make the
GUI look better and improve user experience.

User is unable to mark a StudentRecord of a Student that does
not exist inside the Student list.

Let's fix the bug by marking student records, not students.

UG does not include example usage and general usage of TAskmaster.

Let's improve the UG to include said usages.

When the window is resized to a smaller window, some parts of the window
become white.

Let's fix this bug by setting the background color of the base
AnchorPane.

Session buttons, student and student record cards are too big.

Visual space in TAskmaster can be better utilised, allowing the user
to see more information at once.

Let's redesign said components.
